Package com.example.sip

Class Summary
Borough Borough is an object containing information for one of the thirty two boroughs of London....In total thirty two instances of a Borough are going to be used in the execution of the program.
BoroughProfileActivity This activity contains information of the screen called Boroughs Profile.
BoroughStore Borough Store is an object where all the instances of boroughs are stored in an array list.
GLCube This class creates the 3d cube used for the view of the Welcome Activity
GLRenderer This class initialises the 3d cube, the start time and the frames for the animation that is used for the view of the WelcomeActivity.
GLView This class is responsible for the view of the WelcomeActivity
ListResultActivity This activity contains information for the screen where the borough results are shown on a list in scholarships function.
LondonMapActivity This activity contains a google map object and boroughs are added on the map in the form of a mark.
MainActivity This activity is the main screen of the program.
MapBoroughResultActivity This activity is used by two other activities to show Borough results on the map.
MapSchoolResultActivity This activity contains information for the screen that is responsible to show on a google map the results(schools) which the user has selected before in SchoolListActivity.
MyArrayAdapter This class contains information of the list that is created to support the list view for the ListResultActivity class.
MyDatabase This class makes use of a third party library which uses the SQLite classes and supports reading databases bigger than the maximum file size for the assets folder.
ScholarBoroughActivity This activity represents the screen that asks the user to select ranges for unemployment and crime rate to see the results.
ScholarSchoolActivity This activity contains information for the Scholarships by Schools screen.
School School is an object containing information for a specific school in London..There exists 714 schools in the database hence during execution there will be 714 instances of the school object.
SchoolListActivity This activity is responsible for the screen showing results which are schools in a form of list.
SchoolStore SchoolStore is an object containing an array list of all the schools used in the program
UnemploymentActivity UnemploymentActivity is a class that manages the screen of the Unemployment Scheme function.
WelcomeActivity Welcome Activity is the first screen that user can see during the execution of the program.
